Troops of the Operation Safe Conduct on Saturday  apprehended three hoodlums on motorcycle at Iwaraja Junction, Osun State, who were going towards Ilesa East Local Government Area to disrupt smooth conduct of 2019 general elections in that area.
The hoodlums were arrested with items ranging from a locally made pistol, three rounds of cartridges, mobile phones, iPad, Peace Corps face cap and  ID card and a the sum of N14,300.
The Acting Director Army Public Relations, Colonel Sagir Musa, stated that those arrested will be handed over to the police upon completion of initial profiling and investigation.

			
